---
import Layout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import JsonLd from '~/components/common/JsonLd.astro';

const metadata = {
  title: 'Natural vs Synthetic Fabric — Which Is Right for Your Product?',
  description: 'Compare natural fibers (cotton, wool, linen) and synthetic fibers (polyester, nylon, spandex) across performance, sustainability, comfort, and cost.',
  ignoreTitleTemplate: true,
};
---

<Layout metadata={metadata}>
  <JsonLd
    type="Article"
    article={{
      headline: 'Natural vs Synthetic Fabric — Which Is Right for Your Product?',
      description: 'Compare natural fibers (cotton, wool, linen) and synthetic fibers (polyester, nylon, spandex) across performance, sustainability, comfort, and cost.',
      datePublished: '2026-07-07',
    }}
    data={{ url: 'https://seekingtex.com/compare/natural-vs-synthetic' }}
  />
  <JsonLd type="BreadcrumbList" breadcrumbs={[{ name: 'Home', href: '/' }, { name: 'Compare', href: '/compare' }, { name: 'Natural vs Synthetic' }]} />
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto py-24 px-6">
    <a href="/products" class="text-sm text-sky-600 hover:text-sky-700">&larr; Products</a>
    <h1 class="mt-4 text-4xl font-semibold text-gray-900">Natural vs Synthetic Fabric</h1>
    <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-gray-500">A practical comparison between natural and synthetic fibers — understand the strengths and limitations of each for your product application.</p>

    <div class="mt-12 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
      <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-2xl p-8 border border-gray-200">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">Natural Fibers</h2>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm text-gray-600">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-sky-500 mt-2 flex-shrink-0"></span><span><strong>Breathability:</strong> Excellent natural breathability. Cotton and linen are highly absorbent and comfortable.</span></li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-sky-500 mt-2 flex-shrink-0"></span><span><strong>Comfort:</strong> Soft, natural hand feel. Hypoallergenic options (organic cotton, bamboo).</span></li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-sky-500 mt-2 flex-shrink-0"></span><span><strong>Sustainability:</strong> Biodegradable, renewable resources. Organic options avoid pesticides.</span></li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-sky-500 mt-2 flex-shrink-0"></span><span><strong>Durability:</strong> Lower tensile strength than synthetics. Prone to shrinkage, wrinkling, and UV degradation.</span></li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-sky-500 mt-2 flex-shrink-0"></span><span><strong>Best for:</strong> Daily wear, luxury apparel, baby clothing, towels, bedding, casual fashion.</span></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-2xl p-8 border border-gray-200">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">Synthetic Fibers</h2>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm text-gray-600">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-emerald-500 mt-2 flex-shrink-0"></span><span><strong>Performance:</strong> Moisture-wicking, quick-dry, waterproof, UV protection — engineered for specific functions.</span></li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-emerald-500 mt-2 flex-shrink-0"></span><span><strong>Durability:</strong> High tensile and tear strength. Abrasion-resistant. UV stable with additives.</span></li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-emerald-500 mt-2 flex-shrink-0"></span><span><strong>Easy Care:</strong> Wrinkle-resistant, shrink-resistant, quick-drying. Machine washable with minimal ironing.</span></li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-emerald-500 mt-2 flex-shrink-0"></span><span><strong>Sustainability:</strong> Recycled options available (GRS certified). Not biodegradable but recyclable.</span></li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-emerald-500 mt-2 flex-shrink-0"></span><span><strong>Best for:</strong> Sportswear, outerwear, tactical gear, workwear, swimwear, performance apparel.</span></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <section class="mt-16 bg-gradient-to-br from-sky-50 to-blue-50 rounded-2xl p-8 border border-sky-200">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">Which Should You Choose?</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Choose <strong>natural fibers</strong> for everyday comfort, luxury apparel, and products where biodegradability and renewable sourcing are priorities. Natural fibers excel in casual wear, baby clothing, and bedding. Choose <strong>synthetic fibers</strong> for performance applications — sportswear, outdoor gear, tactical wear, and any product requiring moisture management, waterproofing, or durability. Many modern products use blends — combining natural comfort with synthetic performance. Seekingtex specializes in high-performance synthetic fabrics with eco-friendly recycled options.</p>
      <div class="mt-6 flex gap-4 flex-wrap">
        <a href="/products" class="px-6 py-3 bg-gray-900 text-white rounded-full text-sm font-medium hover:bg-gray-800 transition">Browse Products</a>
        <a href="/guides" class="px-6 py-3 border border-gray-200 text-gray-700 rounded-full text-sm font-medium hover:border-gray-400 transition">Buying Guides</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </section>

  <section class="sr-only" data-ai-block="definition" aria-hidden="true">
    <p>Comprehensive comparison between natural fibers (cotton, wool, linen) and synthetic fibers (polyester, nylon, spandex). Covers breathability, comfort, sustainability, durability, care, and cost. Natural fibers offer breathability, biodegradability, and natural comfort but are less durable, prone to shrinkage, and lack technical performance. Synthetic fibers offer moisture-wicking, quick-dry, waterproof, UV protection, and durability but are not biodegradable and are petroleum-based. Recommendation: natural for everyday/luxury, synthetic for performance/outdoor, and blends for combining strengths of both.</p>
  </section>
</Layout>
